notes.text:
An update for the idm:DL1 module is now available for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 8.

Red Hat Product Security has rated this update as having a security impact of Important. A Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE link(s) in the References section.
notes.title: Topic

notes.text:
Red Hat Identity Management (IdM) is a centralized authentication, identity management, and authorization solution for both traditional and cloud-based enterprise environments. 

Security Fix(es):

* slapi-nis: NULL dereference (DoS) with specially crafted Binding DN (CVE-2021-3480)

For more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.

notes.text: A flaw was found in slapi-nis. A NULL pointer dereference during the parsing of the Binding DN could allow an unauthenticated attacker to crash the 389-ds-base directory server. The highest threat from this vulnerability is to system availability.
notes.title: Vulnerability description

notes.text: slapi-nis: NULL dereference (DoS) with specially crafted Binding DN
notes.title: Vulnerability summary

notes.text:
This vulnerability affects Directory Server with the Schema Compatibility plugin "slapi-nis". To verify if an instance is configured with Schema Compatibility: 
$ ldapsearch -b 'cn=Schema Compatibility,cn=plugins,cn=config' -s base

Red Hat Identity Management is affected by this flaw.
notes.title: Statement

notes.text: The CVSS score(s) listed for this vulnerability do not reflect the associated product's status, and are included for informational purposes to better understand the severity of this vulnerability.
notes.title: CVSS score applicability

remediations.details:
For details on how to apply this update, which includes the changes described in this advisory, refer to:

https://access.redhat.com/articles/11258
Red Hat has investigated whether a possible mitigation exists for this issue, and has not been able to identify a practical example. Please update as soon as possible.

vulnerabilities.title: slapi-nis: NULL dereference (DoS) with specially crafted Binding DN
